{"nodes": [{"id": "claude_conversion_plan", "label": "Python conversion plan (port physics core, replace STLM with SciPy)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Port only the ~500-line physics core to Python; do NOT port the ~6300-line STLM Lanczos library. Build the Hamiltonian as a dense symmetric NumPy matrix (packed triangular storage unnecessary since NPOINT <= 1000). Keep Colbert-Miller kinetic matrix elements exactly as in BUILD. Load potential parameters from a config file replacing Constantes2.txt. Preserve fort.4 output values/units for regression comparison."}, {"id": "claude_scipy_replacement", "label": "SciPy eigensolver replacement (eigh subset_by_value / eigsh)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "scipy.linalg.eigh(H, subset_by_value=(ELOW, EHIGH)) or subset_by_index reproduces STLM's eigenvalue-window behavior; scipy.sparse.linalg.eigsh (Lanczos, same algorithm family as STLM) only if N grows large."}, {"id": "claude_verification", "label": "Regression verification against committed fort.4 / fort.97", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Run the Python port with the same fort.3 input (A=13.04, B=30.20, NPOINT=500, AMASS=218947.07152) and diff eigenvalues against committed fort.4 (first level ~9.7211221 cm-1) and fort.97 (we ~19.5309196 cm-1); energies should match to ~1e-6 cm-1."}, {"id": "claude_file_io_map", "label": "File I/O map (Fortran unit numbers = fort.N filenames)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "c